text: Garmisch-Partenkirchen (; ) is a Landkreis (district) in Bavaria, Germany. The district is located in the Bavarian Alps and includes the highest mountain of Germany, the Zugspitze (2962 m). ==Towns and municipalities== The district includes no towns.
